            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_179gc' title='Col. 179GC &mdash; HL Deb 23 May 2002 vol 635 c179GC' name='column_179gc' href='#column_179gc' rel='bookmark'>179GC</a>
            a multiplicity of ways for the money to come to the Post Office according to what is most convenient and according to the facilities the Post Office itself enters into in discussion with the banks. The point is that cash will be available, without charge, based on benefits or based on tax credits, in the local post office for people, as it is now.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
